## Proposed Changes

### Option A: Dual Calendar Modes (RECOMMENDED)

**Implement TWO calendar presentations:**

1. **Dashboard Widget (NEW)** - Compact calendar for quick overview
   - Mini month view (current month only, no scrolling)
   - Event count badges on dates (e.g., "3 events")
   - Click date → open full calendar page OR expand mini agenda
   - Size: ~300-400px wide, fits in dashboard grid
   - Color-coded event dots (not full event details)

2. **Full Calendar Page (EXISTING)** - Professional scheduling tool
   - Keep existing month/week/day/agenda views
   - Optimize for deep calendar work (scheduling, recurring events, drag-drop)
   - Add view density toggle (compact/comfortable/spacious)

**Benefits:**
- ✅ Dashboard users can see calendar at a glance (Notion-style)
- ✅ Power users still have dedicated full calendar page (Google Calendar-style)
- ✅ Better aligns with "everything in one dashboard" vision
- ✅ Reduces need to navigate between pages constantly

### Option B: Calendar-First Dashboard Tab

**Create "Calendar" tab in Dashboard with integrated view:**
- Left: Mini calendar widget (compact month view)
- Right: Upcoming events list (next 7 days)
- Bottom: Quick add event form

**Benefits:**
- ✅ Consolidates calendar into dashboard workflow
- ❌ Loses dedicated full-screen calendar power

### Option C: Keep Standalone, Improve Compact Design

**Keep calendar on dedicated page, optimize UX:**
- Further compact month view (smaller day cells, tighter spacing)
- Add mini month picker in sidebar
- Better mobile responsiveness

**Benefits:**
- ✅ Simple, no architectural changes
- ❌ Doesn't solve "too isolated" concern

